The paper deals with the analysis of network codes for packet line networks, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of chunked codes and overlapped chunked codes also involves the manipulation of data packets, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the potential application of OCC for multimedia transmission, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
